# Example secrets file for act (GitHub Actions local testing)
# 
# To use with act, create a .secrets file (don't commit it!) or use:
# act --secret-file .secrets
#
# Format: KEY=value
#
# For testing CI jobs (test job):
# No secrets required - it just runs pytest

# For testing Docker Hub publish job:
# DOCKER_USERNAME=your-dockerhub-username
# DOCKER_TOKEN=your-dockerhub-personal-access-token

# For testing Artifactory publish job:
# ARTIFACTORY_URL=https://your-artifactory-instance.com
# ARTIFACTORY_REPO=your-repo-name
# ARTIFACTORY_USERNAME=your-artifactory-username
# ARTIFACTORY_PASSWORD=your-artifactory-password-or-api-key

# For testing Render deployment job:
# RENDER_API_KEY=your-render-api-key
# RENDER_SERVICE_ID=your-render-service-id

# Note: Docker Hub publish only runs on tags (v*.*.*)
# To test locally with act, you can use:
# act push --eventpath test-event.json --secret-file .secrets --job docker-hub

